parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To sow, spread, scatter. Probably strengthened from spao; to scatter, i.e. Sow.
Animal, natural, sensuous. From psuche; sensitive, i.e. Animate.
Body, flesh; the body of the Church. From sozo; the body, used in a very wide application, literally or figuratively.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I wake, arouse, (b) I raise up. Probably akin to the base of agora; to waken, i.e. Rouse.
Spiritual. From pneuma; non-carnal, i.e. ethereal, or a spirit, or supernatural, regenerate, religious.
Body, flesh; the body of the Church. From sozo; the body, used in a very wide application, literally or figuratively.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.
